        walkthrough = '1. Talk to Hieronymus\n2. Exit to North Gustaberg (S), follow the wall to the west to find the Allied Ensign.\n   - Party of 3 or greater required.\n3. Once the party leader has selected to enter, you will be transported into Ruhotz Silvermines.\n4. At the start, two Cadet Woundpatchers will pop.  Speak to them to have them follow you to a room to the north with 10 wounded solders.\n5. Speaking to the Woundpatchers will show the following menu options:\n   - Give the physician orders.\n     - Commence healing, stat!\n     - Specify healing methods.\n     - Prescribe what type of treatment?\n     - Cures and physical healing.\n     - Status ailment recovery.\n     - Offer moral support.\n     - Rest and recover.\n     - Issue no orders.\n6. When you are close to a solder who is injured, use the "Commence healing, stat!" command to order the Woundpatcher to use cure spells.  (You must issue the command each time you wish her to cure.)\n   - If a solder says "P-p-poisoned...  C-c-can\'t b-b-breathe..." or "You must help me!  I can\'t move my arms or legs!", use the "Prescribe what type of treatment?" option and chose "Status ailment recovery" to switch the Woundpatcher to use the appropriate status spells.  (Be sure to issue the "Commence healing, stat!" command after, and use the "Prescribe what type of treatment?" option to change back to "Cures and physical healing" mode.)\n   - When a solder is sufficiently cured, his/her name will turn green and will say "I owe you my life. Many thanks!".\n   - Woundpatchers can and will run out of MP meaning that they will have to rest their MP before they can continue.\n   - If the Woundpatcher says "I\'m not sure I\'m cut out for this...", use the "Offer moral support" option.  (But do not use it too often, as it seems to annoy the Woundpatchers.)\n7. When four solders are cured, you will get the message that the operation is complete.  (But you are still able to cure the final wounder solder.)  Return to the Dawn Aureola to receive your XP and finish the Campaign Op.\n   - You will not receive XP if you are too far from the Dawn Aureola.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Cut and Cauterize III (S)'] = {
        id = 73,
        start_npc = 'Rasdinice',
        start_zone = 'Southern San d\'Oria (S)',
        start_pos = 'I-9',
        description = 'Our injured have been evacuated to Everbloom Hollow. Join the Knights of the Iron Ram in East Ronfaure (G-5) and help tend to the wounded.',
        reward = '~2500 Experience Points\n~3500 Allied Notes',
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Talk to Rasdinice.\n2. Travel to East Ronfaure (hug the left wall as soon as you come out).\n3. Once the party leader has selected to enter, you will be transported into Everbloom Hollow.\n4. After a few moments, two healer NPCs (Pupil Palliator I and II) will load\n   - Talk to them to make them follow you.\n5. The Healers have four options when you talk to them:\n   - Ask them to heal - the NPCs heal a nearby NPC.\n   - Change their prioritization - the NPCs will be either more or less likely to cast Poisona / Paralyna\n   - Offer moral support\n     - Healer morale constantly decays (possibly only when in range of the NPCs messages).\n     - You want to use this every 5 or so Cures, or after they /heal.\n     - If you use it too frequently, it won\'t have any effect.\n     - If the NPC runs away, they will return to the start of the zone until you use this.\n     - You can use this right when they start to run away and then they will just touch the starting point and turn around and return to you.\n     - If the NPC runs away, you will get a depressed message when you use this for the rest of the run and it might not work.\n     - Pupil Palliator II\'s morale seems to decay faster than I.\n   - Rest and relax - /heal to recover MP. This seems to be faster than if they run out of MP and are forced to rest.\n6. The healer AI...\n   - When asked to heal, they cast Cure II, III, or IV (randomly) and can cast Paralyna / Poisona if their target is enfeebled.\n     - Even in status removal mode, they are not forced to remove statuses and it can take quite a few tries\n   - When starting or finishing an action, including changing their prioritization or resting, the NPCs can decide they have had enough and run back to the start.\n     - They will return to the person with claim on them after they have taken a lap.\n   - When they try to cast a spell that they do not have the MP for, the NPCs will /heal\n     - They seem to recover MP slower this way than if you ask them to /heal.\n7. You will need to heal 10 other injured NPCs scattered throughout the maze by talking to the healers and telling them to heal.\n   - These NPCs spawn with between 40 and 60% HP.\n   - Their names will turn Green and they will be considered healed when their HP reaches 95% and their status ailments are removed.\n     - NPCs can either be Poisoned or Paralyzed.\n     - NPCs cannot die from poison.\n   - There are six enfeebled NPCs this time.\n     - Norvallen Knight (South H-8)\n     - Aragoneu Knight (South H-8)\n     - Scarlet Boar Esquire (South I-8)\n     - Royal Guard (North H-8)\n     - Royal Knight (North I-8)\n     - Savage Hound Condottiere (North I-8)\n8. When you have healed 8 of the 10 injured NPCs, the Objective will be complete\n   - If you leave at this point, you will receive a middling appraisal. You must heal all of the NPCs for an enthusiastic review.\n   - If going for a full clear, it is recommended to switch the NPCs to status removal mode and run to the enfeebled NPCs first.\n9. You must leave via the Dawn Aureola or you will not get credit.\n10. Return and talk to Rasdinice for your reward.',
        notes = nil,
    },
