    ['Steel Resolve I (W)'] = {
        id = 491,
        start_npc = 'Emhi Tchaoryo',
        start_zone = 'Windurst Waters (S)',
        start_pos = 'H-9',
        description = 'Allied strongholds must be fortified to withstand assault by Beastman siege turrets. Travel to one of our nation\'s areas and oversee the construction effort.',
        reward = '80 Experience Points \n460 Allied Notes',
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. After speaking with Emhi Tchaoryo, proceed  to a Windurst controlled Campaign area.\n2. Proceed to the Fortification tower in the zone, and speak to the active Campaign arbiter.\n3. Upon speaking to the Campaign arbiter at a Windurstian controlled Fortification, s/he will describe the individuals involved in the reconstruction of the Fortification, their appearance, and what crystals they will require to do their job.\n4. After agreeing to continue, you will be given a straight-on view of one side of the Fortification and NPCs will begin running in from the bottom, waiting for a crystal, then running out the left or the right after being given the correct one or after being ignored long enough.\n5. The basis of this Campaign Op is to choose the correct element crystal for the NPCs standing at the Fortification.\n6. You must choose the correct element from a menu for any of the NPCs actively standing still at the Fortification.\n7. The menus and correct NPC choices are as follows (with simplified notes):\n   - Menu 1\n     - Fire: Elvaan man in a Smithy\'s Apron and a red hat (red hat = fire)\n     - Ice: Tarutaru female with blonde pigtails and a Field Tunica (blonde taru = ice)\n     - Wind: Hume female in a Goldsmith\'s Apron (hume girl = wind)\n   - Menu 2\n     - Earth: Elvaan man in Woodworker\'s Apron and a black Voulge on his back (axe = earth)\n     - Lightning: Mithra in a Dark Cloak (cloak = lightning)\n     - Water: Tarutaru male in a blue Aketon (blue taru = water)\n   - Menu 3\n     - Light: Hume male in Jujitsu Gi and a Jaridah Khud (hume guy = light)\n     - Dark: Elvaan female in Chocobo Jackcoat and Walahra Turban (elvaan girl = dark)\n8. You must wait until the NPC has stopped approaching the Fortification before they can receive a crystal.\n9. Choosing the correct element for any NPC currently standing at the Fortification will result in an a crafting animation for that NPC immediately followed by them running back out of the scene.\n10. Choosing the wrong element will make you less likely to pass the operation successfully and also delay the menu from reappearing for a short duration.\n11. Allowing an NPC to leave without a crystal will not mark you down as much as choosing incorrectly will.\n12. Upon successful completion of the operation, you will receive 80 Experience Points.\n13. Return to Emhi Tchaoryo to complete your mission and receive 460 Allied Notes.',
        notes = nil,
    },
